{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Warmup\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}], \"model\": \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001", "id": "msg_01T6D68FdEtXpLLY8bMqw2v3", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hello! I'm Claude Code, Anthropic's CLI file search specialist. I'm ready to help you navigate and explore your codebase.\n\nI can assist you with:\n\n- **Glob patterns** - Find files by naming conventions and file types\n- **Grep/Regex** - Search file contents with powerful pattern matching\n- **Read** - View specific file contents\n- **Bash operations** - List directories, check file structures, and more\n\nYour repository is currently on `branch_1` and appears to be in a clean state. The recent commits show:\n- 08396db: Stuff\n- bdfe0e6: app.py commit\n- c8b6c54: add some cool data\n- 27519d3: initial commit\n\nWhat would you like to search for or explore in your codebase? Feel free to ask me to:\n- Find files matching certain patterns\n- Search for specific code or text\n- Read and analyze file contents\n- Explore the directory structure\n\nI'm ready when you are!"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 495, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 229, "service_tier": "standard"}}}
